
[1]contagious

   CONTAGIOUS, a.

   1. Containing or generating contagion; catching; that may be
   communicated by contact, or by a subtil excreted matter; as a
   contagious disease.

   2. Poisonous; pestilential; containing contagion; as contagious air;
   contagious clothing.

   3. Containing mischief that may be propagated; as contagious example.

   4. That may be communicated from one to another, or may excite like
   affections in others.

   His genius rendered his courage more contagious.
